DAIP is an AI-powered enterprise knowledge assistant that enables employees to securely search, understand, and interact with internal banking documents using Generative AI and Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG). Instead of manually searching through documents, users ask questions in natural language and receive accurate, context-aware answers with references to the original documents.

What it does
Uploads internal documents (PDF, Word, Excel, text).
Parses and chunks document content.
Generates vector embeddings for semantic search.
Stores vectors in PostgreSQL using pgvector.
Stores document metadata in MongoDB/PostgreSQL.
Performs hybrid search (semantic + keyword).
Retrieves the most relevant document chunks.
Uses an LLM to generate grounded answers.
Returns citations and document sources.
Supports domain-based filtering (HR, Compliance, Legal, Payments, ESG, etc.).
Maintains secure authentication using JWT.
Technology Stack
Backend: Java, Spring Boot
Database: PostgreSQL + pgvector
Metadata: MongoDB/PostgreSQL
AI: OpenAI/Ollama embedding model + LLM
Search: Hybrid Semantic + Keyword Search
Frontend: React
Security: Spring Security + JWT
Deployment: Docker, Kubernetes, GCP
Architecture Flow
User
   │
   ▼
React UI
   │
   ▼
Spring Boot REST API
   │
   ▼
RAG Pipeline
   │
   ├── Embed Query
   ├── Semantic Search (pgvector)
   ├── Keyword Search
   ├── Merge Results
   ├── Build Context
   ▼
LLM
   │
   ▼
AI Response + Source Citations
Business Benefits
Reduces document search time from minutes to seconds.
Provides trustworthy AI answers grounded in enterprise documents.
Minimizes hallucinations through RAG.
Improves employee productivity.
Protects sensitive banking information by using internal knowledge only.
Can be extended for compliance, risk, ESG, legal, operations, and customer support use cases.
One-line Elevator Pitch

DAIP is an enterprise AI knowledge platform that combines RAG, semantic search, and Large Language Models to deliver fast, accurate, and secure answers from Deutsche Bank's internal documents.